## PROMPT STARTS HERE

You are documenting a multi-module Spring Boot microservices e-commerce project. It has grown across 6 iterations (v1 → v6), currently consisting of these services:

- `eureka-server` (8761) — service registry
- `api-gateway` (8000) — Spring Cloud Gateway, single entry point, JWT validation, role/user-id header forwarding
- `product-service` (8081) — Postgres `product_db`, Category + Product + ProductView entities, seller ownership
- `user-service` (8082) — Postgres `user_db`, User entity, JWT issuance, role selection (CUSTOMER/SELLER/ADMIN)
- `order-service` (8083) — Postgres `order_db`, Order + OrderItem entities, cart/checkout/payment/notification orchestration
- `recommendation-service` (8084) — stateless, co-purchase + co-view scoring
- `payment-service` (8085) — Postgres, mock deterministic payment processing
- `notification-service` (8086) — no DB, sends real email via Gmail SMTP
- `frontend-service` (8080) — Thymeleaf, no JS, calls everything through the gateway

Before writing anything, **scan the actual codebase** (all `pom.xml`/`build.gradle` files, all `@RestController`/`@Service`/`@Entity`/`@Configuration`/`@FeignClient` classes, `application.yml`/`application.properties` in every module, and every custom filter/interceptor/exception class) so that what you produce reflects the real, current state of the code — not a guess based on service names alone. If something below doesn't match what you find in the repo, trust the repo and flag the mismatch to me instead of silently "correcting" your output to match this prompt.

Produce **two separate markdown documents**, generated one at a time — finish and show me Document 1 in full before starting Document 2.

